title: Grateful Dead Live at Broome County Arena on 1983-04-12
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Keep On Growing, Bird Song, Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, Cassidy, Loser, It's All Over Now, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Let It Grow

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Not Fade Away, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: mr.wonderful Awesome show, didn't start this tour till Rochester, 4-15, caught 8 shoows in 9 nights though ! My buddy Clay had root canal before this show, and PHIL ripped him apart ! LOL, NOT REALLY

Our captain fell in love with a lady like a dove... Love the sound of this matrix..Kudo's~!! The spring and fall of 83' smoked and this show is a primal example..Well played from start to finish..Jerry's voice sounds pretty dam good..It lists  KEEP ON GROWING as the 2nd song, but GREATEST STORY is the actual 2nd song played this nite..This show IMHO is a must have from 83'~!! GIVE IT A WHIRL>>> Forever Grateful>Forever DEAD...Let your life proceed by it's own design

1983 is very under rated I was fortunate enough to be at this show. I think 1983 was a very under rated year. Started seeing the grateful dead in 1977 and never looked back until the end in 1995. Some years were much better than others. This was definitely an "on" year. Love this show as well as the St Stephen shows in The Garden and at Hartford. 

Was at Ithaca college at the time and many of us went since it was so close. Outstanding show from start it end - especially the end when the crowd just would not stop clapping in rhythm to the NFA beat so the band came back for the encore by starting it with NFA. Just outstanding

St. Stephen Perhaps? I was attending college in Rochester and me and two buddies drove down for this show, meeting some other friends from downstate who were driving up.  I was hoping for a St. Stephen as they played it the last time they were here - alas it was not to be. I would have to wait until later in the year and Hartford for that gem to make an appearance.  A good show with a smoking second set - one continuous piece of music.  The Other One sticks out in my mind.  One other thing that sticks out was getting into the venue.  They were funneling us all thru a single wide door opening before you could get to the ramps going into the venue.  Now I'm a pretty big guy (250 lbs. or so back then) but I clearly remember being lifted off my feet for a good 5-10 feet while trying to get thru that door.  I've not had that happen before or since - it was crazy but the boys made it all worth while.

- A very overrated show. Garcia sounds miserable and very self-unaware. The mix on this matrix is somewhat vocal-heavy, unfortunately like a soundboard, emphasizing the croaking. OK show, but I'd be disappointed if it were my first, after hearing their reputation from seasoned heads.
